        <title>Workstation KDE error</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[Algernon]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>No, more RAM is usually better. But in case you would have had a low overall amount of RAM in your PC you could have decreased the RAM for the gateway while increasing the one for the workstation. But you seem to have plenty of RAM so nevermind. Sometimes the DE needs a while to come up, you could maybe try to take a look into the logs or change the graphics settings or driver and see if it helps.</p>
